1
00:00:00,860 --> 00:00:07,070
Tradingview recently introduced a new chart
type, the High Low chart, and for price action

2
00:00:07,070 --> 00:00:09,769
traders, this could be of great help.

3
00:00:09,769 --> 00:00:15,659
Today I’ll show you how to read price action
using High Low charts and you’ll also learn

4
00:00:15,659 --> 00:00:20,360
how to easily find trends and trade with the
current momentum.

5
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:28,590
You know the drill, like, subscribe, and stick
around for the full video.

6
00:00:28,590 --> 00:00:31,410
High-Low chart

7
00:00:31,410 --> 00:00:36,340
The High-Low chart is located in the chart
type selection menu.

8
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:42,900
Bars are built based on the value of the maximum
and minimum prices for a given timeframe.

9
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:48,690
The price values for which the chart was built
are displayed on each bar, below and above

10
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:50,780
the bar.

11
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:56,580
This type of chart basically removes the open
and close price, and instead, you see the

12
00:00:56,580 --> 00:01:01,580
range in which the value changed, on your
timeframe.

13
00:01:01,580 --> 00:01:06,640
If you want to customize it, in the Chart
Settings, you can change the color of the

14
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:08,750
bars and text.

15
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:13,960
I personally don’t have a problem with the
fact that I don’t see the red and green

16
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:15,729
color of the candles.

17
00:01:15,729 --> 00:01:22,700
By having the same color on up and down candles,
you’ll actually trade in a neutral/ unbiased

18
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:25,760
state of mind.

19
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:31,020
This chart looks weird at first, because you
don’t see the open and close.

20
00:01:31,020 --> 00:01:33,760
You are only seeing a range.

21
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:39,480
But from a price action perspective, if you
are a trader who is analyzing highs and lows

22
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:44,000
in price, this is very helpful.

23
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:49,720
Most traders are looking at major market swings
when they are analyzing highs and lows and

24
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:51,510
determine trends.

25
00:01:51,510 --> 00:01:57,119
But you can also analyze highs and lows of
individual candlesticks.

26
00:01:57,119 --> 00:02:04,690
With the High Low chart, reading price action
of individual candlesticks is super easy.

27
00:02:04,690 --> 00:02:11,560
When the high and the low of the recent candlestick
is higher than the high and low of the previous

28
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:17,230
candlestick, market is in a bullish momentum
and buyers are controlling the market.

29
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:18,760
There is buying pressure.

30
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:26,370
When the low and high of the recent candlestick
is lower than the low and high of the previous

31
00:02:26,370 --> 00:02:32,310
candlestick, market is in a bearish momentum
and sellers are controlling the market.

32
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:38,270
You see just how easy it is to read price
action, bar by bar.

33
00:02:38,270 --> 00:02:41,700
Candlestick simplified

34
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:49,330
Now, using the High low chart presents an
opportunity to simplify candlestick trading.

35
00:02:49,330 --> 00:02:54,300
If you are that type of trader that memorized
dozens of candlestick formations, you’re

36
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:58,580
in luck, because you don’t have to over-complicate
things.

37
00:02:58,580 --> 00:03:04,200
With this type of chart, there are only 4
candlestick formations.

38
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,730
First candlestick formation is the bullish
candle.

39
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:15,490
A bullish candle has a higher high and a higher
low compared to the previous bar.

40
00:03:15,490 --> 00:03:18,860
Second formation is the bearish candle.

41
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:24,180
Bearish candlesticks have a lower high and
a lower low, again, compared to the previous

42
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:25,980
bar.

43
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:32,720
Third type is the inside candlestick, which
has a lower high and higher low relative to

44
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,269
the previous bar.

45
00:03:34,269 --> 00:03:39,570
This bar is contained within the range of
the previous candlestick.

46
00:03:39,570 --> 00:03:45,129
Even if the high or the low are equal to the
previous candlestick, it’s still an inside

47
00:03:45,129 --> 00:03:47,510
bar.

48
00:03:47,510 --> 00:03:54,069
Last formation is the engulfing candlestick,
which has higher high and lower low relative

49
00:03:54,069 --> 00:03:58,239
to the previous bar
And even if either the high or the low are

50
00:03:58,239 --> 00:04:04,650
equal to that of the previous bar, it’s
still an engulfing bar.

51
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:11,269
So this is the foundation of your price action
analysis: bullish and bearish candlesticks,

52
00:04:11,269 --> 00:04:14,220
inside candles and engulfing candles.

53
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:21,059
It’s time to train your eyes to easily spot
each formation, on a high low chart.

54
00:04:21,059 --> 00:04:25,360
Open any chart, and start reading price action.

55
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:31,430
We have both highs and lows that are lower
than the previous bar, so this is a bearish

56
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:32,850
candlestick.

57
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:35,409
Another bearish candlestick.

58
00:04:35,409 --> 00:04:37,349
And another one.

59
00:04:37,349 --> 00:04:39,069
Another bearish candle.

60
00:04:39,069 --> 00:04:45,770
Here’s the first inside bar, with a lower
high and higher low compared to the previous

61
00:04:45,770 --> 00:04:48,300
bearish candle.

62
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:50,509
Next is a bearish candle.

63
00:04:50,509 --> 00:04:52,629
Another bearish candle.

64
00:04:52,629 --> 00:04:54,879
Another one.

65
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:56,559
Another bearish candle.

66
00:04:56,559 --> 00:04:59,869
Again, a bearish candlestick.

67
00:04:59,869 --> 00:05:01,509
Bearish candle once again.

68
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:07,680
Okey, we have our first engulfing candle,
with a higher high and lower low compared

69
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:10,060
to the previous bar.

70
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:12,259
Another bearish candlestick.

71
00:05:12,259 --> 00:05:18,080
Next is a bullish candlestick, with a higher
high and a higher low compared to the previous

72
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,860
bar.

73
00:05:19,860 --> 00:05:25,020
Another bullish bar and now trend seems to
change to the upside.

74
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:27,020
Bullish candlestick again.

75
00:05:27,020 --> 00:05:29,229
Another bullish candle.

76
00:05:29,229 --> 00:05:31,919
Next is an engulfing candle.

77
00:05:31,919 --> 00:05:34,249
Bearish candlestick.

78
00:05:34,249 --> 00:05:36,770
You see just how easy is to read price action.

79
00:05:36,770 --> 00:05:41,919
I’ll say it again, you don’t need to memorize
other candlestick combinations.

80
00:05:41,919 --> 00:05:48,520
So, to get used to high low charts, the first
thing is to start reading candlesticks until

81
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:52,819
it becomes very easy to determine which type
is.

82
00:05:52,819 --> 00:06:00,349
6 Price action rules
Now, you might ask, how is this useful to

83
00:06:00,349 --> 00:06:01,349
trade?

84
00:06:01,349 --> 00:06:02,610
It’s simple.

85
00:06:02,610 --> 00:06:07,839
Once you know to recognize these candlesticks,
you’ll then determine the state of the current

86
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:09,059
trend.

87
00:06:09,059 --> 00:06:13,580
To find the current trend, you follow 6 easy
rules.

88
00:06:13,580 --> 00:06:14,580
1.

89
00:06:14,580 --> 00:06:19,550
If you have consecutive bullish bars, you
are in a minor uptrend.

90
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:21,009
2.

91
00:06:21,009 --> 00:06:24,590
Consecutive bearish bars indicate a minor
downtrend.

92
00:06:24,590 --> 00:06:25,729
3.

93
00:06:25,729 --> 00:06:32,039
A bullish candle starts an upswing and confirms
the end of a downswing.

94
00:06:32,039 --> 00:06:33,069
4.

95
00:06:33,069 --> 00:06:39,150
A bearish candle starts a downswing and confirms
the end of an upswing.

96
00:06:39,150 --> 00:06:40,360
5.

97
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:43,110
Inside candlesticks are neutral bars.

98
00:06:43,110 --> 00:06:47,839
They don’t affect the direction of the current
swing, because they do not break the previous

99
00:06:47,839 --> 00:06:49,180
high and low.

100
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:56,479
So an inside bar after a bullish or bearish
candlestick don’t change the current trend.

101
00:06:56,479 --> 00:06:57,479
6.

102
00:06:57,479 --> 00:07:02,939
Engulfing candlesticks introduce uncertainty
into the market structure, because they break

103
00:07:02,939 --> 00:07:05,389
both the previous high and low.

104
00:07:05,389 --> 00:07:09,999
But, we’ll give the benefit of the doubt
to the current swing.

105
00:07:09,999 --> 00:07:15,520
So, engulfing candlesticks in an upswing continue
the upswing.

106
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:20,610
Engulfing candlesticks in a downswing continue
the downswing.

107
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:28,339
Now, let’s look at the previous example
and let’s mark the main swings, based on

108
00:07:28,339 --> 00:07:33,479
the bars that changed the direction of the
market swings.

109
00:07:33,479 --> 00:07:41,499
These bars are inside candlesticks and engulfing
candlesticks and they do not affect the direction

110
00:07:41,499 --> 00:07:44,129
of the market swings.

111
00:07:44,129 --> 00:07:51,489
Let’s change markets and find the market
swings based on this system.

112
00:07:51,489 --> 00:07:58,490
You simply look for bullish candles to start
an upswing and to confirm the end of a downswing.

113
00:07:58,490 --> 00:08:05,300
And for bearish candles to start a downswing
and to confirm the end of an upswing.

114
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:12,259
And you include the inside candlesticks and
engulfing candlesticks in the respective swing.

115
00:08:12,259 --> 00:08:17,610
First we have a downswing, with many consecutive
bearish candles.

116
00:08:17,610 --> 00:08:26,219
Then, an upswing, this is the candle which
interrupts the previous down leg.

117
00:08:26,219 --> 00:08:32,649
And another downswing, this is the candle
which ends the upswing.

118
00:08:32,649 --> 00:08:40,450
Then market forms an upswing, and another
downswing.

119
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:43,709
Upswing once again.

120
00:08:43,709 --> 00:08:53,790
Then I see a choppy period, with a small downswing,
a small upswing and another downswing.

121
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:57,279
And finally, another upswing.

122
00:08:57,279 --> 00:09:01,050
This analysis might seem very simple and unimportant.

123
00:09:01,050 --> 00:09:06,790
But if you understand how the swings are marked
and you see the swings clearly, you will identify

124
00:09:06,790 --> 00:09:12,150
the current direction of the market with ease,
at any point in time.

125
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:17,310
Support and Resistance trading

126
00:09:17,310 --> 00:09:23,050
I found that high low charts are great to
trade support and resistance, and are also

127
00:09:23,050 --> 00:09:28,990
a good filter to eliminate false breakouts,
when price moves beyond a previously established

128
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:34,579
price range but then retreats back to within
the range.

129
00:09:34,579 --> 00:09:40,139
As you probably know, one of the classic rules
of support and resistance is that support,

130
00:09:40,139 --> 00:09:50,149
once violated, becomes resistance and conversely,
resistance, once violated, becomes support.

131
00:09:50,149 --> 00:09:55,459
With high low charts, and the previous swing
recognition technique, you can find decent

132
00:09:55,459 --> 00:10:00,540
trades around major levels in the market.

133
00:10:00,540 --> 00:10:07,310
So on this GBP/USD hourly time frame, we see
an uptrend, with price trading around this

134
00:10:07,310 --> 00:10:10,670
resistance level.

135
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:19,680
We have a candle breaking the previous high,
and a quick retracement below the level.

136
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:25,600
After a small consolidation, we have a valid
breakout.

137
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:31,439
So a decent signal would be at the re-test
of the previous level, when the downswing

138
00:10:31,439 --> 00:10:35,709
is ended with a bullish candlestick.

139
00:10:35,709 --> 00:10:39,170
Here’s the signal.

140
00:10:39,170 --> 00:10:45,670
I like to enter when the high of the bullish
candle is broken, but you can also enter immediately

141
00:10:45,670 --> 00:10:48,279
after you see the candle.

142
00:10:48,279 --> 00:10:53,140
Stop goes below the most recent swing and
we’ll be conservative and we’ll set a

143
00:10:53,140 --> 00:11:00,930
risk to reward ratio of 2.

144
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:07,069
You see how using this type of chart helped
us to avoid the first fake out and allowed

145
00:11:07,069 --> 00:11:14,350
us to enter, in the direction of the main
trend, when a new upswing was forming.

146
00:11:14,350 --> 00:11:19,069
Liquidity clear-outs

147
00:11:19,069 --> 00:11:25,000
Another great way is to trade liquidity clear-outs
in the direction of the main trend.

148
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:30,790
If you watched my previous smart money manipulation
video, you know I like to join the market

149
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:33,850
after a false breakout.

150
00:11:33,850 --> 00:11:39,080
Markets hunt for stop orders and activity
beyond significant price levels.

151
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:45,959
If this breakout occurs and fails, there will
be many trapped traders, which can add momentum

152
00:11:45,959 --> 00:11:48,740
to the opposite direction from that level.

153
00:11:48,740 --> 00:11:54,930
The best trades of this type occur in direction
of the main trend.

154
00:11:54,930 --> 00:12:05,050
In this example, we have a clear downtrend,
with price currently in consolidation.

155
00:12:05,050 --> 00:12:12,610
For a short entry, the market trades above
this resistance area, and immediately reverses

156
00:12:12,610 --> 00:12:18,800
on the following bars and closes back under
the resistance.

157
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:22,889
There no real continuation beyond the level.

158
00:12:22,889 --> 00:12:29,509
And when the price forms a bearish candlestick,
which ends the previous upswing, we can take

159
00:12:29,509 --> 00:12:38,279
a short trade, after this liquidity clear-out,
in the direction of the main trend.

160
00:12:38,279 --> 00:12:45,270
Stop goes above the previous swing high, and
we’ll target this next swing low in the

161
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:49,680
price structure.

162
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:55,070
Here’s another example.

163
00:12:55,070 --> 00:13:04,060
We have a clear support, in an obvious uptrend,
with the price being unable to continue lower.

164
00:13:04,060 --> 00:13:10,939
We then have a small breach below support,
but price immediately closed back above the

165
00:13:10,939 --> 00:13:13,970
support level.

166
00:13:13,970 --> 00:13:20,259
Once the movement was confirmed by a bullish
candle, the wiser trade would be a long trade,

167
00:13:20,259 --> 00:13:24,180
instead of chasing the failed breakout.

168
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:29,999
Stop loss is placed below the previous swing
low, and we’ll target this next swing high

169
00:13:29,999 --> 00:13:38,110
in the price structure.

170
00:13:38,110 --> 00:13:42,250
In some way, high low charts eliminate some
market noise.

171
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:45,990
You don’t see the wicks, the red or green
candles.

172
00:13:45,990 --> 00:13:52,529
I can see the market swings and the support
and resistance levels very easy using high

173
00:13:52,529 --> 00:13:54,620
low candles.

174
00:13:54,620 --> 00:14:00,460
You see, many traders follow market swings
in a wrong manner and find them useful only

175
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:02,199
in hindsight.

176
00:14:02,199 --> 00:14:07,490
They are unable to apply the concept of market
swings in real-time.

177
00:14:07,490 --> 00:14:13,040
With this chart, and following some basic
price action rules you will know exactly the

178
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:19,100
current price wave you are in, and with a
solid understanding of support and resistance,

179
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:47,529
you will find good areas to trade from.

180
00:14:47,529 --> 00:15:45,910
Of course, there are lots of other methods
to trade high low charts, involving volume

181
00:15:45,910 --> 00:15:53,999
and even with indicators, divergences in particular
work very well in combination with these candles.

